    "recap_headline": "Duke University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HIGH POINT, N.C.\n- Duke fell behind early and couldn't catch High Point, eventually falling, 12-6, at Williard Stadium on Tuesday, March 10. The Panthers (10-7) scored six runs in the first inning, and the Blue Devils (13-6) got within three, 6-3, in the third inning, but couldn't complete the rally.\nCollin Anderson\nand\nJake Lambdin\nboth left the yard for Duke, while\nKaden Smith\nled the Blue Devils' offense with three RBI.\nTyler Albright\nworked four walks, his new career high for free passes in a game.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nHigh Point got on the board first, scoring six runs in the bottom of the first.\nAfter a clean second frame for both teams, the Blue Devils cut the deficit in half with three runs in the top of the third.\nCollin Anderson\nled off the inning with a home run to left-center field, his second time going yard this season.\nAfter a\nJake Lambdin\ndouble and swipe of third,\nTyler Albright\nworked a walk to put two on for\nKaden Smith\n, who brought both home with a double, to make it a 6-3 affair.\nThe hosts responded with three runs of their own in the bottom of the fourth, with a pair of RBI singles and a third run coming home after a throwing error.\nAnother RBI double from Smith, once again scoring Albright, made it a 9-4 ballgame in the top of the fifth\nThe Panthers expanded the margin back to six runs, 10-4, after a balk brought home a run in the bottom\u00a0half of the frame.\nAnderson continued his strong day at the plate in the top of the sixth, driving in\nAnthony Runfola\nwith an RBI single.\nHigh Point moved in front, 12-5, with a pair of run-scoring singles in the bottom of the sixth.\nThe Blue Devils scored the final run of the contest in the top of the eighth, with a two-out homer from Lambdin on a full count, for the final scoreline of 12-6.\nUP NEXT\nDuke (13-6, 1-2 ACC) returns home to host Miami (12-4, 1-2 ACC). The Blue Devils and Hurricanes will start the series with a 6 p.m. first pitch on Friday, March 13.\nFor more information on Duke baseball, follow the Blue Devils on\nTwitter\n,\nFacebook\nand\nInstagram\nby searching for \"DukeBASE\".\n#GoDuke"
